The paper focuses on expert finding in bibliographic networks, which involves analyzing textual content and authority ranking. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of embedding learning and network structure analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Deep Learning (cs.DL) and Database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the large-scale dataset used in the experiments suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC) sub-category.
